<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-21T01:57:00-05:00" n="1135" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1135">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4614.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate, Ciudad
                                    Juárez</hi></placeName>,<lb/>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1912-07-21T00:00:00-06:57">undated</date>] (<hi rend="italic">Received August 12, 1912—11.26
                                p.m.</hi>)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>According to General Orozco, President Madero is to resign in pursuance
                            of a basis for cessation of hostilities which he claims has been agreed
                            upon, to be concluded with General Huerta soon. Casas Grandes district
                            now in control of Federals; conditions better.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>